            "questionNumberWithinTopic": 4,
            "tags": [
                "Lexical Analysis",
                "Finding the Tokens",
                "Compiler Design"
            ],
            "question": {
                "text": "A lexical analyzer uses the following patterns to \nrecognize three tokens T1, T2 and T3 over the \nalphabet {a, b, c}. \n\nT1: a ? (b│c)* a \n\nT2: b ? (a│c)* b \n\nT3: c ? (b│a)* c \n\nNote that x?  means 0 or 1 occurrence of the symbol \nx. Note also that the analyzer outputs the token that \nmatches the longest possible prefix.  \n\nIf the string bbaacabc is processed by the analyzer, \nwhich one of the following is the sequence of tokens \nit outputs?",
                "images": [],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            },
            "options": [
                {
                    "id": "A",
                    "text": "T1  T2  T3",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "B",
                    "text": "T1  T1  T3",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "C",
                    "text": "T2  T1  T3",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "D",
                    "text": "T3 T3",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                }
            ],
            "correctAnswer": [
                "D"
            ],
            "solution": {
                "text": "Given,  \n\nHere, x? means 0 or 1 occurrence of the symbol x. \n\nWe can represent x?  as  + x using regular \nexpression. \n\nGiven string: b b a a c a b c \n\nT1 can generate upto: bba \n\nT2 can generate upto bb \n\nT3 can generate upto bbaac \n\nSo, we can see T3 can generate longest prefix of \ngiven string.  \n\nAgain, check remaining portion of input for next \nlongest prefix generator.  \n\nString left: a b c \n\nT1 cannot generate abc, it can generate abca but we \nrequire only abc \n\nT2 cannot generate abc, it can generate ab, but not \nabc \n\nT3 can generate abc.  \n\nSo, T3T3 is the correct sequence of tokens for the \ncomplete input. Hence. option d is correct answer.",
                "images": [
                    "assets/Compiler Design/CD_Lexical_Analysis_P7_X733.png"
                ],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            }
        }
